    <text id="A3052T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Carson writes to Ms. Miller asking that she send food or clothing, though they
                    are not close, now that he has been told that authorities will allow it
                through.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Mrs. Virignia L. Miller<lb/>York<lb/>York County Pennsylvania
                    <name type="recipient">Mrs V.L. Miller</name>
                    <name type="place">Officers Barracks <abbr expan="Fort">Ft.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Delaware">Del.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-04-10">April 10th 65</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Madam</salute>
                </opener>

                <p> We have received instructions this morning from the Federal authorities that we
                    would be permitted to receive anything in the way of clothing or eatables that
                    may be sent us by our friends- whilst it is true I have but little acquaintance
                    with you I at the same time look upon you as a friend, and will be very thankful
                    for anything you may send. I arrived at this place on the 13th of March from
                    Hilton Head S.C. where six hundred of us had been confined since last <abbr
                        expan="August">Aug</abbr>. I have heard nothing from home since my arrival
                    here, consequently can give you no news from that quarter. The two McCutchins
                    &amp; Henry Wright are still here. My respects to Mr. Miller.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours in haste</salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="Samuel">Saml</abbr> F. Carson 1st <abbr expan="Lieutenant"
                            >Lieut</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Company">Co</abbr> "D" 5th <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Infantry">In</abbr><lb/>Division 34</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
